  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 53, 1.448523}", 
    "history" -> {"14.3", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"out-of-time-order correlator", "OTOC"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "BravyiScramblingSimulate[in, {a, b}, spec, ..., dep] simulates quantum \
information scrambling circuits of depth 0, 1, 2, ..., dep and returns the \
list of the absolute values of the out-of-time-order correlator (OTOC) \
between two local unitary operators a and b with respect to the initial \
Bravyi state in. For the remaining arguments spec, ..., see \
RandomBravyiCircuit. BravyiScramblingSimulate[..., {dep, ds}] simulates \
circuits of depth 0, ds, 2 ds, ..., dep in the forward-time evolution part. \
BravyiScramblingSimulate[in, {i, j}, ...] assumes a := f i + f_i^\\[Dagger] \
and b := 1 - 2 f_j^\\[Dagger] fj, where fk is the k^th fermion mode. \
BravyiScramblingSimulate[in, i, ...] is equivalent to \
BravyiScramblingSimulate[in, {i, 1}, ...].", "synonyms" -> {}, 
    "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "BravyiScramblingSimulate", "titlemodifier" -> 
    "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> "BravyiScramblingSimulate", 
    "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/BravyiScramblingSimulate"}},
